  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(AFAD) Enhance capacity of flood affected women-headed households for lifesaving economic/livelihood</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A total of 1,400 female headed households will get conditional cash grant of BDT. 10,000 each and will also provide livelihood training on different options. Beneficiaries will be able to restore their livelihoods through the cash grant and will be a big support to their families to regain the lost by monsoon flood in July and August 2019.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project will focus on short-term live saving economic recovery interventions as a temporary solution to the flood crisis in line with the Humanitarian Response Plan FS sector phase 2 objective &#x201C;to recover from the stress caused by the flood on agriculture, livestock, access to food (physical &amp; economic) and livelihood opportunities, which complement food insecurity and build resilience against future shocks&#x201D;. Therefore, funds will be utilized to simulate local recovery for economic/livelihood opportunity to ensure lifesaving and dignity of 1,400 female-headed households in three most affected district of Jamalpur</narrative>
  </description>
